Hey, forward it to your respective hostel groups.


Hello everyone!

We have all gone through that phase when we watched cartoons and wonder how
the magic happens. Many of us even harbor dreams of someday mastering
animation and making such cartoons.

In order to make those dreams a reality, we, the Animation Club of CFI, in
collaboration with Techsoc, bring to you a series of 3D Animation
sessions, focused on developing animation models from basics. There are 3
sessions planned for this purpose. Tentative schedule of these sessions:


Session

Date

Time

Venue

Session1

4th April,2016

8:00 PM

CRC 101

Session2

6th April, 2016

8:00 PM

CRC 101

Session3

8th April, 2016

8:00 PM

CRC 201

Topics that will be covered:

    Primitive 3D modeling with hands on examples.
    Subdivision modeling with hands on examples.
    Demonstration on 3D Sculpting.
    Materials and Texture with hands on examples.
    Light and Camera Setup with hands on examples.
    Scene set up and Rendering with hands on examples.
    Demonstration on Special Effect Simulations.


This will be followed by a 3D Animation Event. The event will focus on
whatever you have learnt during these sessions. Participants will be given
a time limit within which they have to come up with a 3D model.

Event details:

Date: 10th April, 2016
Time: 10:00 AM
Venue: CRC 101


In case of any queries, please contact the coordinators:

Pavan K
Ph no.  +91 9176484600
